Group ride (no-drop) Biking with Baddies Monthly Sunday rides, Women only Instagram, Website.

Last Sunday of every month. 2:00 PM 

Start: Logan Park 690 13th Ave NE

“All levels welcomed, no one left behind. Always refer to the website for updates. Come out with your bike and make new friends. There may be people you know, and/or folks that might want to get to know you on this ride. Even if that’s not the goal, come outside to cycle with us in nature.”

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Wedge Live Emergency Bike Ride. Event page.

When: Every Sunday at 7pm. Roll at 7:30pm. Aug 24, 2025, Aug 31, 2025

Start: Mueller Park (Colfax and W 25th St)

Distance: ?. Pace: Conversational, likely 8-12 mph.

What is an emergency bike ride? It's an immediate, systematic, coordinated response among partners at all levels, to the community's need for more bike rides.

Who can participate? Anyone of any skill level who feels an urgent need to ride your bike at a leisurely conversational pace in a group setting.

Are scooters ok? Yes.
items.location: Mueller Park, 2509 Colfax Ave South, Minneapolis, MN 55405, USA

items.description:
Group ride (drop) Tuesday Night Rides. Facebook.

When: Tuesdays. Meet at 5:45 pm, roll at 6:00 pm. Aug 19, 2025, Aug 26, 2025

Start and Finish: HeadFlyer Brewing

Two pace groups. Spicy: 14-16 mph pace for 20-25 miles Mild: 11-13 mph pace for 15-20 miles.

Routes published on Monday in the FB group. Rides feature a mid-ride restaurant stop and have the option to end back at Headflyer for a pint. There are no sweeps, so this can be a drop ride. Bring lights, lock, helmet, flat-fixing kit, anything you need to get yourself home.
items.location: HeadFlyer Brewing, 861 E Hennepin Ave #100, Minneapolis, MN 55414, USA

items.description:
Race (CX) Versus cross III. Instagram

When: Sunday Oct 19, 2025. 9am-4pm

Where: Huset Park, Columbia Heights. 

Cost: TBA (reg opens Sept 1), but typically $25-35/race, with a $10 “citizen” race for people new to the sport.

The best cyclocross race in Minnesota is back for its third year! Come race and spectate at Huset Park in Columbia Heights. Get some food from @kramarczuks and @nordicdogs612, chat all things bike fit, strength programming and PT with @go_physio_mn, and hang with our other vendors and sponsors! There will be a kids race and face painting—stick around for our signature Tracklocross race and raffle at the end of the day! Registration Opens September 1—stay tuned!
items.location: Huset Park, 3965 Jefferson St NE, Columbia Heights, MN 55421, USA

items.description:
Race (CX) SSCXWC Instagram, Registration, FAQs

When: Thursday-Sunday Oct 2, 2025 - Oct 5, 2025.

Cost: $120 (scholarships available for trans, non-binary, or BIPOC riders) 

Location: Various sites around Mpls TBA. The main race on Sunday is at Buck Hill

Single-speed cyclocross world championship. Weekend is full of events, including bandit cross on Thursday, a group ride and packet pick-up party on Friday, “feats of strength” on Saturday, and the main cyclocross race event on Sunday at Buck Hill. See the BikeReg or FAQ page for full details.

Group ride (no-drop) Midwest Dirt Legion, Full moon theo ride Ride Details. Instagram.

Date: Tuesday Oct 7, 2025 6:00 PM - 8 PM.

Location: The Trailhead (Theo Wirth)

Who’s this for: “MDL hosts events specifically for marginalized genders. FTW / anyone but cis-men are welcome at our rides! Here’s a great resource defining FTW from our friends at GreaseRag.”

OPEN GROUP RIDE: All skill levels welcome and we will break into groups as necessary so we all have a fun ride! This is a no drop ride so plan for plenty of time to stop and chat, scope out features, and generally bring the stoke!

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
items.location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

Group ride (no-drop) Chainlink ride Instagram

When: Saturday Oct 18, 2025 1:00 PM. 1:45 pm roll-out.

Start and Finish: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop

Distance: Likely 8-10 miles. Pace: Casual 8-12 mph.

Organized by @bonesawcyclingcollective, @ez.bikeclub, @andstillweride, @bikingwithbaddies

Bringing the whole community together for a ride you don’t want to miss! Expect music, a photobooth, a videographer to capture the vibes, and a pit stop at Surly Brewing. This will be a casual ride. Think sexy pace, chill pace, a ride where you can feel the laughs. We will have Marshall’s and Mechanics on hand for safety. Pull up on whatever bike you have! Road bike, BMX bike, gravel, cruiser, whatever you got on two wheels hell even tricycles are welcomed.

items.summary: SSCXWC Welcome Party and Packet pick-up
items.description:
Gathering SSCXWC Welcome Party and Packet pick-up. Instagram, Registration, FAQs

When: Friday Oct 3, 2025 6:00 PM 6-10pm+.

Cost: Free and open to the public. (you don’t have to be registered for SSCXWC, bring your friends!)

Location: Arbeiter Brewing Company

6:00pm Packet pick up opens

7:00pm Betty Won't

7:45pm 2026 host comp #1

8:15pm Cowboy Thoughts

9:30pm Packet pick up closes

10:00pm Group roll-out to secret afterparty spot

Locals, this is your only chance for packet pickup, so be there! All registered racers get a free SSCXWC x Wilde Bikes musette bag filled with goodies including your Wolf Tooth commemorative top cap. Live music, dancing, burgers from Francis, and beer!
items.location: Arbeiter Brewing Company, 3038 Minnehaha Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) SSCXWC Feats of Strength. Instagram, Registration, FAQs

When: Saturday Oct 4, 2025 9:00 AM Roll at 10am. 

Cost: Must be registered for SSCXWC

Start: Sea Salt (4825 Minnehaha Ave) Finish: TBA at the start of the ride.

Distance: ~30 miles. 

9:00am Free Coffee + Breod Pudain

9:45am Announcements

10:00am Feats of Strength roll-out starts. Finish around 4pm.

You'll be placed in a group with other racers and led around town to partake in challenges and chilling. Earn enough pOOchie buxxx and you'll score a start-line advantage at Sunday's race!

In addition to FREE coffee and bread puddin', Sea Salt is selling beermosas, spam musubi or beet musubi you can pack for the day, and more. Each group will stop for a free cookout lunch.

Wear a bathing suit, pack extra water + snacks, and be ready to be on your bike for ~30 miles. Groups will end in various locations around MPLS, not at Sea Salt. This ride is only for registered SSCXWC25 racers.
items.location: Sea Salt, 4825 Minnehaha Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55417, USA

items.description:
Race (CX) SSCXWC main race Instagram, Registration, FAQs

When: Sunday Oct 5, 2025 10am-4pm.

Cost: $120 (scholarships available for trans, non-binary, or BIPOC riders) 

Location: Buck Hill

Single-speed cyclocross world championship. 

9:30am Party bus meets at Southside Preservation Society (reservation ONLY)

10:00am Race check-in opens

11:00am Course opens for pre-ride

12:15pm Men's Taters race (45 Mins)

1:30pm Non-binary & Gender Expansive race +

Women's Open race (45 Mins)

2:45pm Men's Tots race (45 Mins)

3:30pm 2026 host comp #3

4:30pm Party bus departs from Buck Hill (reservation ONLY)


Racers will get a free brat or veggie burger as well as a free special edition SSCXWC beer. Additional drinks can be purchased at a discount with your racer wristband. 


The races are only for registered SSCXWC25 racers, but we encourage spectators to attend! Dogs are allowed. There will be alcohol and scantily clad bicyclists-bring children at your own discretion.
items.location: Buck Hill, Burnsville, MN 55306, USA

items.description:
Gathering SSCXWC Awards party. Instagram, Registration, FAQs

When: Sunday Oct 5, 2025 7:00 PM 7pm-10pm.

Cost: Must be a registered SSCXWC rider.

Location: Familia Skateboard Shop


7:00pm Doors

7:30pm Prophets of Mothra

8:30pm Awards

9:00pm 2026 host comp/winner announcement


Hug your new friends and cheer for the cities vying to host SSCXWC in 2026. Flash and winners' tattoos by Goons. Portraits of non-binary and transgender cyclists from Erik Mathy's "We've Always Been Here" project will be on display. This party is only for registered SSCXWC25 riders.
items.location: Familia Skateboard Shop, 835 E Hennepin Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55414, USA

items.description:
Race (CX) MCF Tu Night CX. Instagram. Website.

When: Tuesday Sep 30, 2025. 5pm-9pm. 

Start: Ainsworth Park (St. Louis Park)

Cost: All Races are $25, adding a second race is $5. (Some weeks, racing may be free if you volunteer for set-up or teardown. Check with MCF for details) 

This week has an FTW category (for anyone but cis-men) at 6:25pm.

5:00 PM - Beginners & Juniors - (30 minutes)

5:35 PM - Intermediate & Advanced - (40 minutes)

6:25 PM - FTW race (30 min)

Check MCF instagram or website for more details. These are unsanctioned races, so you don’t need a racing license. No Gods, No USAC.

CX is a volunteer-intensive sport and we need all of the setup and tear down help we can get. Nights 6 and 7 will only be possible if we have sufficient crew to staff them. If you or your team are interested in volunteering please email calendarcoordinator@mncyclingfederation.org!
items.location: Ainsworth Park, 7700 W 28th St, St Louis Park, MN 55426, USA

items.description:
Race (CX) Lunch Break Brazing Cross. Registration

When: Sunday Oct 12, 2025. 9am - 5pm. 

Where: 7050 Meadow Grass Avenue South (Cottage Grove Bike Park)

Variety of gender and skill races, as well as “klunker”, single speed, and tracklocross races. See registration link for full schedule. Online registration closes Oct 11th. *On-site day of registration is $35. On-site registration opens at 8 a.m. Sunday and closes 30 minutes before each event. We do not require any sort of license to race. This is an unsanctioned race. 

Each category will have a podium ceremony approximately 15 minutes after their race.
